COMMERCE CITY HALL WILL BEGIN PAPER RECYCLING PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COMMERCE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has decided to establish a program to recycle paper and other 
materials used at City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
The council directed City Administrator Louis Sheppard to develop a recycling 
and conservation program in the next few weeks. In addition to saving office 
paper for recycling, the city will try to use two-sided printing whenever 
possible. 
</P>
<P>
Sheppard also is considering issuing coffee mugs to employees to reduce the 
number of disposable cups used at City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
"We need to determine if all the problems are being addressed before we 
proceed," he said. 
</P>
