<HEADLINE>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG'S NATO AIDE QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government said Wednesday that its ambassador to the North Atlantic Treaty 
Organization, Guy de Muyser, resigned in the wake of U.S. intelligence 
allegations that he passed information to Moscow. 
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Jacques Poos announced the resignation in a statement to 
Parliament. 
</P>
<P>
A NATO spokesman in Brussels said he did not know how serious the security 
breaches were. 
</P>
<P>
De Muyser, 64, had been Luxembourg's ambassador to NATO and Belgium since March 
10, 1986. 
