</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AMRITSAR, India 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bombs apparently planted by Sikh separatists exploded within minutes of each 
other Wednesday aboard two state-owned buses parked in Amritsar's main bus 
terminal, killing at least four people and wounding 36 others, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The bombings came on the second anniversary of Operation Black Thunder, in 
which security forces besieged the Golden Temple of Amritsar, Sikhdom's holiest 
shrine, for nine days to quell an occupation by Sikh militants. Forty people 
were killed. 
