<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
MAN ARRESTED OVER FIRE AT APARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 25-year-old man has been arrested on suspicion of setting fire to the Oxnard 
apartment he shared with his girlfriend, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Lynn Waterloo is being held in the Ventura Jail, in lieu of $100,000 bail, in 
the Sunday fire at the one-bedroom apartment on the 5000 block of Nautilus 
Street, said Capt. Pat Logue, an investigator for the Oxnard Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
The fire, which caused an estimated $10,000 damage, probably was started with a 
match or cigarette lighter, Logue said. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses identified Waterloo as a suspect, and he was arrested at 6:45 p.m. 
Monday, Logue said. 
</P>
<P>
Waterloo apparently had a dispute with his girlfriend, Logue said. She was 
visiting her mother in Camarillo when the fire began, Logue said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA051090-0094 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 216732 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
May 10, 1990, Thursday, South Bay Edition 
</P>
