<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CASINO WILL BE RAZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The former Horseshoe Club in Gardena, the city's oldest casino, will be razed 
in the coming months and replaced with a modern shopping center. 
</P>
<P>
The Gardena City Council approved plans Tuesday night for the 
38,500-square-foot development at Rosecrans and Vermont avenues. The shopping 
center, approved by the Planning Commission last month, will feature two 
fast-food restaurants and a variety of other businesses. It will be developed 
by Emil Neshanian of Encino. 
</P>
<P>
When the 41-year-old club closed last May, Gardena was left with only the 
Eldorado Club and the Normandie Casino, compared to six clubs a decade ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
