<HEADLINE>
<P>
SENTENCE IS 2 YEARS IN METH CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The girlfriend of the president of the San Diego chapter of Hells Angels has 
received a two-year federal prison term for assisting her boyfriend in a 
methamphetamine transaction. 
</P>
<P>
Kathleen Pirelli, 22, of Lakeside, was also fined $10,000 by U.S. District 
Judge John Rhoades. 
</P>
<P>
Pirelli and the motorcycle gang president, Guy Russell Castiglione, 40, also of 
Lakeside, were arrested May 13, 1989, at the Temecula checkpoint after 2 pounds 
of methamphetamine were found in Pirelli's purse. 
</P>
<P>
Castiglione, who pleaded guilty Dec. 20 to possession of methamphetamine with 
intent to distribute, was sentenced by Rhoades on March 5 to five years in 
prison. 
</P>
<P>
Pirelli pleaded guilty the same day to using a telephone in a narcotics 
transaction, which exposed her to a maximum sentence of four years. 
</P>
