<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLY SECURES NO. 1 SEEDING IN CITY 4-A BASEBALL PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At times, the meeting was as confusing as trying to decipher an opposing team's 
signs, but the City Section 4-A Division baseball seedings were made by a panel 
of coaches Wednesday night, with Poly High edging out El Camino Real for the 
No. 1 berth. 
</P>
<P>
Poly (22-3, 17-0 in league play), the East Valley League champion, will play 
host to the winner of a wild-card game in the first round May 18. 
</P>
<P>
El Camino Real (17-2-1, 14-1-1), the West Valley champion, also will play host 
to a wild-card winner in the first round. 
</P>
<P>
The winner of today's North Valley League game between San Fernando (15-6-2, 
10-5-1) and visiting Kennedy (16-8, 11-5) will be seeded third and will play 
host to San Pedro in the first round. The North Valley runner-up will play 
Venice at a site to be determined. 
</P>
<P>
Birmingham (18-6-1, 12-5), the Mid-Valley League champion, will play host to 
Sylmar (16-9, 10-7), the East Valley runner-up. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth (19-5-1, 11-4-1), the second-place team in the West Valley League, 
will play host to Carson (10-4-2 in league play), the Pacific League runner-up. 
</P>
<P>
Monroe (10-10, 8-9), the runner-up in the Mid-Valley, will play at University, 
which won the Western League with a 15-2 mark. 
</P>
<P>
In Wednesday's wild-card games, the winner of today's North Valley League 
showdown between Cleveland and host Granada Hills -- each team has four wins in 
league play -- will visit North Hollywood. Reseda will play at Taft. 
</P>
<P>
Taft (10-13-1, 6-9-1) was seeded first in the wild-card games, followed by 
North Hollywood (9-11, 7-10), the winner between Cleveland (5-14, 4-12) and 
Granada Hills (6-15-2, 4-10-2), and Reseda (5-15, 5-12). 
</P>
<P>
Poly will play host to the lowest-seeded wild-card winner and El Camino Real 
will play host to the second-lowest seeded winner in first-round games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
