<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In other Palomar League games: 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 8, Torrey Pines 1 -- Matt Miller singled, doubled twice, scored 
three runs and drove in two for Mt. Carmel (20-4, 10-1). Preston Bynes singled, 
doubled and homered for Torrey Pines (10-15, 1-10). 
</P>
<P>
Poway 5, Vista 4 -- Vista (10-14-1, 4-6-1) scored four in the bottom of the 
sixth and had the tying run at second base with none out, but Danny Miller 
(10-1) escaped the jam with two of his 12 strikeouts. Ed Thompson, Matt 
Schwenke, Tom Peterson and Miles Kelly each had two hits and an RBI for Poway 
(16-6-1, 8-3). 
</P>
<P>
Fallbrook 9, San Dieguito 6 -- Dan Furleigh hit a three-run homer and Matt 
Dunlap hit a bases-empty homer to lead Fallbrook (10-11, 5-6). San Dieguito is 
2-21-1, 1-9-1. 
</P>
<P>
Avocado League 
</P>
<P>
San Pasqual 6, Escondido 4 -- Ben Duncan and Dave Goss each went three for 
three with two RBIs, Chris Hancock went two for four, and Brian Moss went two 
for two for San Pasqual (10-10-1, 7-2), which moved into a first-place tie with 
idle Oceanside. Escondido fell to 11-10 and 5-4. 
</P>
<P>
El Camino 2, San Marcos 1 -- Pitcher J.T. Patton squeezed home catcher Ricky 
Spears with the winning run in the seventh for visiting El Camino (11-12, 5-5). 
San Marcos fell to 12-10 and 5-4. 
</P>
<P>
Ramona 10, Carlsbad 8 -- Sean Kelly hit his sixth homer, with a man on, to 
break an 8-8 tie. Kelly finished two for four with three RBIs for Ramona 
(5-17-11, 2-8). Carlsbad is 9-17 and 1-8. 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont 2-A League 
</P>
<P>
Santana 5, El Cajon Valley 1 -- Gabe Hernandez had two RBIs without getting a 
hit for Santana (4-1, 18-5). His first came in the fourth inning when the El 
Cajon Valley shortstop bobbled a grounder, and the second came in the sixth 
when the shortstop committed a throwing error. Lance McLure hit a two-run homer 
for Santana. 
</P>
<P>
Valhalla 5, West Hills 1 -- Rey Neder came back from arm problems to win his 
first game of the year for Valhalla (13-12-1, 3-3). He threw a six-hitter and 
struck out 12. 
</P>
<P>
3-A Grossmont League 
</P>
<P>
Helix 5, El Capitan 4 -- Eric Nicholson improved to 10-0 as Helix (3-2, 14-8) 
gave first-place El Capitan (5-1, 17-8) its first league loss. 
</P>
