<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BETS: DENIECE WILLIAMS TO SING AT BENEFIT SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gospel, with a faithful mixture of contemporary R&amp;B and pop, will be 
performed by three-time Grammy award-winning singer Deniece Williams at 7:30 
p.m. Saturday at Ventura High School Auditorium, 2155 E. Main St., Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
The performance is a benefit for the Ventura County Crisis Pregnancy Center, a 
nonprofit organization. 
</P>
<P>
Williams burst onto the music scene in 1978 with "Too Much, Too Little, Too 
Late," a No. 1 duet with Johnny Mathis. 
</P>
<P>
She again topped the singles charts with "Let's Hear It for the Boy" from the 
multi-platinum "Footloose" soundtrack in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
Featured Saturday night will be songs from Williams' latest albums, "Special 
Love" and "So Glad I Know." 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds will go to the crisis center, which offers free pregnancy tests, peer 
counseling and a 24-hour hot line. 
</P>
<P>
All seating is reserved. Tickets are $10, $15 and $20 and are available at 
Rudd's, Lord's Storehouse and Christian Family Supplies locations. Tickets will 
be available at the door after 4 p.m. the day of the concert. 
</P>
<P>
For information, call 656-5327. 
</P>
</TEXT>
