<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GRATEFUL DEAD WON'T BE INVITED BACK TO 
SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bowing to complaints about traffic, loitering and public urination, Cal State 
Dominguez Hills has decided not to invite the Grateful Dead rock band back to 
the campus. The band, which has a devoted following harking back to its roots 
in the counterculture of the 1960s, performed over the weekend at the campus. 
</P>
<P>
"The concert on the campus was peaceful . . . (but) in the interest of good 
relations with the Carson community, we have decided not to invite the Grateful 
Dead back to our campus," university spokesman Richard Turner said. 
</P>
<P>
"That's probably best," said Carson Mayor Vera Robles DeWitt, "because our 
neighborhoods are up in arms about it." 
</P>
<P>
Also, a 19-year-old woman allegedly took LSD outside the concert Saturday, ran 
a red light in Manhattan Beach and broadsided another car, killing a pregnant 
woman and her fetus. Heather Tolles was charged Tuesday with two counts of 
second-degree murder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
