<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
HEARING ON WATER SHORTAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A public hearing to discuss whether the region's water shortage has affected 
Pasadena will be held at 3 p.m. May 22 at City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
Under the city's Water Shortage Procedures Ordinance, if a water shortage is 
found to exist, a volunteer plan to reduce water usage will be put in effect. 
</P>
<P>
The plan uses nine water conservation tactics including prohibitions on hosing 
or washing sidewalks, filling decorative fountains, serving water in 
restaurants unless requested, and watering yards between 10 a.m. and 5 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
