<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL NEWS: 2 LOCAL STUDENTS AMONG PRESIDENTIAL SCHOLARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two San Gabriel Valley students are among 141 high school seniors nationwide 
selected as 1990 presidential scholars. 
</P>
<P>
President Bush and Education Secretary Lauro F. Cavazos announced the names of 
the students last week. 
</P>
<P>
Local scholars are Jennifer S. Frautschi of John Muir High School in Pasadena 
and David S. Parks of Arcadia High School. 
</P>
<P>
Of the 141 scholars, 121 were selected on the basis of academic scholarship, 
leadership, character and commitment to high ideals. They include a man and 
woman from each state; Washington, D.C.; Puerto Rico, and American students 
living abroad, as well as 15 students selected at large. Parks is among this 
group. 
</P>
<P>
The other 20 were selected based on achievements in the creative or performing 
arts. Frautschi is an arts scholar. 
</P>
<P>
The students -- receiving the highest federal honor bestowed upon a graduating 
high school senior -- will visit Washington from June 16-20, attend a White 
House ceremony and receive $1,000 each from the Geraldine R. Dodge Foundation, 
a private philanthropic organization in Morristown, N.J. 
</P>
