<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRENCH TRAIN RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
France's high-speed TGV train broke its own world rail speed record Wednesday 
with a run of just over 320 miles per hour, a spokesman for the national 
railways said. 
</P>
<P>
The record was set near Tours in central France by the train that established 
the previous record of 302 m.p.h. last December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
