<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Entertainment Company Wins Lawsuit: FM Entertainment Inc., which went bankrupt 
after a planned stock offering fell through in 1987, won a $3.5-million jury 
verdict against Morgan Olmstead Kennedy &amp; Gardner, an investment firm. 
</P>
<P>
A Santa Monica Superior Court jury ruled that Morgan Olmstead should pay the 
sum to FM, the company behind such films as "Witness" and "The Golden Child." 
In its suit, FM maintained that Morgan Olmstead reneged on an oral agreement to 
handle the public offering in 1986. The investment company plans to appeal the 
verdict. 
</P>
</TEXT>
