<P>
ANTONOWSKY JOINS COLUMBIA PICTURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL CIEPLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sony Corp.'s Columbia Pictures unit named Marvin Antonowsky to the new post of 
executive vice president and assistant to the chairman. 
</P>
<P>
Antonowsky is a longtime associate of Frank Price, who became Columbia's 
chairman earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
Antonowsky worked as a marketing consultant to Tri-Star Pictures and oversaw 
marketing operations at Universal Pictures and Columbia Pictures when Price 
headed those studios. 
</P>
<P>
Columbia said Antonowsky would assist Price "in all areas" in his new position 
in Burbank. MICHAEL CIEPLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
