<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eight professional football players filed suit against the NFL and its teams, 
charging that the creation of developmental squads amounts to price fixing. 
</P>
<P>
The suit alleged that the league and its clubs last year illegally agreed to 
establish a six-person developmental squad for each team and pay those players 
$1,000 per week over the 16-week season. The suit contends the players could 
have made much more on injured reserve. 
</P>
