<P>
Art Schlichter, former Ohio State and Indianapolis Colt quarterback, was signed 
by the Detroit Drive of the Arena Football League. 
</P>
<P>
Schlichter, 30, last played football in 1988 with the Ottawa Roughriders of the 
Canadian Football League. 
</P>
<P>
He has fought a gambling problem that prompted the NFL to suspend him for the 
1983 season and forced him to file for bankruptcy in 1988. Last October, he 
entered a Las Vegas hospital's 30-day program for treatment of the problem. 
