<P>
BREAKFAST CLUB: Every year at this time the city of Santa Ana invites 1,500 
employees to a free, outdoor feed -- called "The Great American Breakfast" -- 
where supervisors and managers flip pancakes, grill sausage and serve fresh 
strawberries, orange juice and coffee. . . . A more recent tradition began last 
year when some of the homeless who sleep out near City Hall joined in the food 
lines and were fed, and some employees are quietly encouraging them to show up 
again this morning. Kristina Lindgren and David Reyes 
