<HEADLINE>
<P>
1ST MCMARTIN CHILD WITNESS BALKS; 
</P>
<P>
GIRL, 11, RESUMES TESTIMONY, SAYS SHE CAN'T REMEMBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The first child witness in the retrial of McMartin Pre-School molestation 
defendant Ray Buckey balked at resuming her testimony today and finally 
testified that she could not remember anything. 
</P>
<P>
The 11-year-old girl had testified only a short time today when she left the 
witness stand complaining of a stomach ache. Prosecutors conceded that she did 
not want to testify further. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Pam Ferrero said the 11-year-old girl's parents called her 
Wednesday night saying the child was "extremely reluctant" to return for more 
questioning. But the parents agreed to bring her anyway. 
</P>
<P>
Ferrero told Superior Court Judge Stanley Weisberg that the girl expressed the 
same desire not to testify when she arrived at court today but "was trying to 
be cheerful" and agreed to take the stand. 
</P>
<P>
But when Buckey's attorney, Danny Davis, resumed cross-examination, the girl 
appeared uncomfortable. She was on the stand 10 minutes, answering intimate 
questions about her body, when she suddenly announced, "May I be excused? I 
have a stomach ache." 
</P>
<P>
Minutes later she was observed in the hallway sobbing in her father's arms as 
he tried to comfort her. 
</P>
<P>
The judge recessed court to give her time to compose herself and said he would 
take further action if that became impossible. 
</P>
<P>
After about an hour of private talks with prosecutors, the child was escorted 
back into the courtroom and returned to the witness stand. Her father was 
allowed to stand next to her and she clutched a stuffed toy. 
</P>
<P>
However, as she began to testify she answered every question regarding her past 
allegations of sexual misconduct at the school by saying, "I can't remember." 
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Buckey is charged specifically with raping the girl and using a 
foreign object to sodomize her. 
</P>
<P>
The first Buckey trial, the longest and costliest criminal proceeding in U.S. 
history, ended in January with Buckey acquitted of 40 counts of molestation at 
the family-owned preschool in Manhattan Beach. His mother, Peggy McMartin 
Buckey, was acquitted of 12 charges. But the jury deadlocked on 13 counts 
against Buckey, and the district attorney decided to retry him on eight of 
those charges involving three children. 
</P>
<P>
Numerous children in the first trial testified about a "naked movie star game" 
allegedly played at the McMartin school. The current witness made the same 
claim, saying she and other children took off their clothes for the game and 
were photographed nude by Buckey. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities made extensive searches but found no such photographs. 
</P>
<P>
During cross-examination Wednesday, the girl told Davis that her memory was 
vague because "I tried to put the people at the preschool out of my mind." 
</P>
<P>
"Who molested you?" Davis asked. 
</P>
<P>
"Just Ray I think," the girl said. 
</P>
<P>
"Did the lady teachers molest you?" he asked. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't remember," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
