<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS / ITALIAN OPEN; 
</P>
<P>
3RD SEED SANCHEZ-VICARIO UPSET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROME 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canada's Helen Kelesi staged two dramatic comebacks to upset weary third-seeded 
Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario, 6-4, 7-5, in the third round of the Italian Open 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Also reaching the quarterfinals was 14-year-old Jennifer Capriati, who won a 
tough battle against Italy's Laura Golarsa, 6-3, 6-7, (10-8), 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Martina Navratilova, Still bothered by a pulled hamstring, the 
33-year-old Navratilova managed to defeat Italy's Sandra Cecchini 6-4, 3-6, 
6-3. 
</P>
<P>
Sanchez-Vicario took a 4-2 lead in the first set before giving up four 
consecutive games and the set to Kelesi. 
</P>
<P>
The scenario repeated itself in the second set, as Sanchez-Vicario, 18, 
squandered leads of 4-2 and 5-3. 
</P>
<P>
"After I fell behind 4-2 in the first set, I just told myself to relax, and to 
start getting ready for the second," said Kelesi, seeded 11th. "And I started 
playing better." 
</P>
<P>
"I really needed this win today. I played Arantxa twice this year and lost both 
times. I knew that if I lost today, it would be a long time before I beat her 
again." 
</P>
<P>
Sanchez-Vicario said that fatigue had been a factor in the loss. "I think I've 
played too many tournaments in a row," she said. "After seven tournaments this 
year, I'm tired. I gave it everything I had today. I attacked on the important 
points. But my shots kept going long. I guess it just wasn't my day." 
</P>
<P>
Navratilova, who wore a bandage around her left thigh, said the hamstring 
injury bothered her on some points. 
</P>
<P>
"I couldn't get down on some volleys and low balls. But it's better than 
yesterday so I'm encouraged," she said. 
</P>
<P>
Two other seeded teen-agers, 16-year-old Monica Seles and 19-year-old defending 
champion Gabriela Sabatini also reached the quarters. Seles beat Mercedes Paz 
6-1, 6-1 and the fourth-seeded Sabatini eliminated Regina Rajchrtova 6-0, 6-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
