<TEXT>
<P>
The Clippers have been denied permission to discuss their vacant head coaching 
job with Cleveland Cavaliers coach Lenny Wilkens, a spokesman for the Clippers 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
Wilkens just completed his fourth season as the Cavaliers' head coach and has 
one year remaining on his contract. The Cavaliers were beaten three games to 
two in their best-of-five first-round NBA playoff series by the Philadelphia 
76ers earlier this month. 
</P>
<P>
The Clippers announced on April 22, the day the NBA regular season was 
completed, that Don Casey wouldn't be back next season as the team's head 
coach. 
</P>
<P>
The Clippers were 30-52 this season, their best record since they went 32-50 in 
1985-86. 
