<HEADLINE>
<P>
MR. FRISKY ARRIVES AT PIMLICO TO READY FOR THE PREAKNESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BALTIMORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mr. Frisky, the 3-year-old colt from Puerto Rico who went off as the favorite 
in last weekend's Kentucky Derby but finished eighth, arrived at Pimlico Race 
Course Wednesday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Nine horses were flown in Wednesday to await the 115th running of the Preakness 
Stakes on May 19. 
</P>
<P>
Mr. Frisky, who was unbeaten in 16 races, faded in the stretch at Churchill 
Downs. 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's flight from the West Coast, which made a stop in Louisville, Ky., 
also brought Preakness hopefuls Land Rush, Kentucky Jazz and Music Prospector. 
</P>
<P>
Pleasant Tap, who took third in the Derby, arrived earlier in the week. 
</P>
